    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nthe diff shown by K shows the diff in a markdown \"fence: with `filetype=markdown`\n\n    ```diff\n    ...\n    ```\n\n<img width=\"448\" height=\"242\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/3ddd9483-c6ed-48a9-900b-64a72e0263f3\" />\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nshow the actual diff content and set `filetype=gitcommit` ?\n\n\n<img width=\"528\" height=\"405\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/5a3705f8-575c-4acf-8caf-07a88d61993c\" />\n\ncc @echasnovski ",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> the diff shown by K shows the diff in a markdown \"fence: with `filetype=markdown`\n\nThis is because it comes from in-process LSP server as a [`textDocument/hover`](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/c37aacb4264232a817246a497e10830fc8837706/runtime/lua/vim/pack/_lsp.lua#L273-L303) method. It only supports [markdown or plain text](https://microsoft.github.io/language-server-protocol/specifications/lsp/3.17/specification/#markupContent), so using markdown here seems reasonable.\n\nThe solution that I've been advocating for is to bundle `diff` tree-sitter parser along with `markdown` one. As tree-sitter is auto enabled in markdown files, this should automatically make diffs highlighted as expected.",
            "created_at": "2026-06-14T14:09:44Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/40239#issuecomment-4701994746",
