        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "> But I wonder how bad it would be if we \"extend\" `textDocument/hover` to support `gitcommit` as a content type.\n\nMy guess is that unexpected problems will emerge. Not even mentioning that built-in LSP in-process implementation doesn't follow the LSP specification and allows something outside of `vim.lsp.protocol.MarkupKind`.\n\n---\n\nI've just read more carefully the spec and it seems that hover can be [`MarkedString`](https://microsoft.github.io/language-server-protocol/specifications/lsp/3.17/specification/#markedString), i.e. `{ language: string; value: string }`. But the comment says this is \"an equivalent to markdown: ```${language}\\n${value}\\n```\". So not sure how this is handled in `vim.lsp`.buf.hover.",
            "created_at": "2026-06-14T14:28:05Z",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/40239#issuecomment-4702039220",
