        {
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "`MarkedString` sounds like exactly what we need! \n\n> equivalent to markdown: `${language}\\n${value}\\n`\". So not sure how this is handled in `vim.lsp`.buf.hover.\n\nTo me that sounds like it's saying the `{value}` should be treated as `{language}`, thus maps pretty nicely to 'filetype' , or at least a treesitter parser-name ... but it's surely client-defined how to render a particular language.\n\nAnd yes this may require enhancing `vim.lsp.buf.hover`",
            "created_at": "2026-06-14T14:34:32Z",
